#  Palay Rover (Autonomous Rice Field Rover)

A Raspberry Pi–based autonomous rover using:
- Camera vision (OpenCV + Picamera2)
- ArUco marker control system
- Dual motor drive system (via GPIO → optocoupler → motor driver)

---

##  Hardware Setup

### Raspberry Pi 5 GPIO → Optocoupler → Motor Driver → DC Motors

The system uses electrical isolation for safety and reliability.

### Suggested Motor Wiring

| Motor | GPIO Pin |
|------|----------|
| Left PWM | GPIO 17 |
| Left DIR | GPIO 27 |
| Right PWM | GPIO 18 |
| Right DIR | GPIO 22 |

> NOTE: Motor power must come from external battery (NOT Raspberry Pi)

